The paper discusses the dynamics of deep neural networks, which is a topic related to neural networks (cs.NE) and machine learning (cs.LG). The analysis of the complexity of the dynamics involves concepts from dynamical systems theory (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also uses mathematical tools such as Lyapunov exponents, which are commonly used in the study of chaos theory (cs.DS).
